ENTRY            A0896   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A0896001   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 10         29
TITLE      The new isotope 110-270 and its decay products 266Hs
           and 262Sg
AUTHOR     (S.Hofmann, F.P.Hessberger, D.Ackermann, S.Antalic,
           P.Cagarda, S.Cwiok, B.Kindler, J.Kojouharova, B.Lommel,
           R.Mann, G.Muenzenberg, A.G.Popeko, S.Saro, H.J.Schoett,
           A.V.Yeremin)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,10,5,2001)
INSTITUTE  (2GERGSI,3SLKUB,3POLWWA,4ZZZDUB)
FACILITY   (LINAC,2GERGSI) The UNILAC accelerator and the
           velocity filter SHIP (Separator for Heavy-Ion
           reaction Products) at GSI.
SAMPLE     (82-PB-207,ENR=0.924) The 207Pb target was prepared
           from enriched (92.4%) material. Metallic lead was
           evaporated on a carbon foil 36 ug/cm2 to a thickness
           of 435 ug/cm2. The lead was then covered by a carbon
           foil of 10 ug/cm2 thickness. The thicker carbon foil
           was oriented up- stream and a charge equilibration
           foil 60 ug/cm2 carbon was mounted downstream at a
           distance of 16 cm from the target.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) The evaporated residues (ERs) were separated
           from the beam by the velocity filter SHIP and
           implanted into a position-sensitive strip Si detector
            (focal-plane stop detector)
           (SISD)
METHOD     (TOF)
STATUS     (TABLE,,S.Hofmann+,J,EPJ/A,10,5,2001) Value from the
           text on p.6.
HISTORY    (20110816C) SB
           (20260206U) SD: Small corrections in Subent 001.
ENDBIB              29
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        A0896002   20110816   20111102   20111031       A073
BIB                  3         12
REACTION   (82-PB-207(28-NI-64,N)110-DS-270,,SIG)
DECAY-DATA (110-DS-270-G,,A,11030.)
           Alpha decay (11.03+-0.05 MeV) measured
           Half-life is 100+-140,40 micro-sec
           (110-DS-270-M,,A,10950.,,A,11150.,,A,12150.)
           Alpha rays of energy (10.95+-0.02), (11.15+-0.02) and
            (12.15+-0.05) MeV were attributed to the decay of the
           isomer.
           Half-life is 6.0+-8.2,2.2 msec) measured
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S). The error bar represents the statistical
           uncertainty only, systematic deviations may change the
           cross-section value up to a factor of two.
ENDBIB              12
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 3          1
EN         DATA       ERR-S
MEV        PB         PB
317.       13.        5.
ENDDATA              3
ENDSUBENT           20
ENDENTRY             2
